I think you need to configure a spring boot **InfluxDb** class instance and then reference it as stated in the documentation using *beanName*.

This can be created using spring boot auto configuration:

 - https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/docs/current/reference/html/boot-features-nosql.html#boot-features-connecting-to-influxdb
 - https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/docs/current/api/org/springframework/boot/autoconfigure/influx/InfluxDbAutoConfiguration.html

According to [Spring AnnotationNameGenerator][1] the name of the default (from the yml auto configured bean) should simply be `influxDB`. We can also look at [the bean definition code][2] and confirm it is creating an `InfluxDB` class instance.

So then configure `influxdb://influxDB` in camel.


----------


Besides auto configuring this alternative should work too (untested - [source][3]):

```
@Configuration
public class AppConfig {
    @Bean(name = &quot;myInflux&quot;)
    public InfluxDb influxClient{
        return InfluxDBFactory.connect(databaseURL, userName, password);
    }
}
```

And then configure `influxdb://myInflux` in camel.


  [1]: https://docs.spring.io/spring/docs/current/javadoc-api/org/springframework/context/annotation/AnnotationBeanNameGenerator.html
  [2]: https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-boot/blob/master/spring-boot-project/spring-boot-autoconfigure/src/main/java/org/springframework/boot/autoconfigure/influx/InfluxDbAutoConfiguration.java
  [3]: https://www.baeldung.com/java-influxdb

